				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12270315/scp-4215#post-4444000</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 12 Dec 2019 08:51:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>lvdoomien</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1593312</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><strong>SQUID TANK SQUAD</strong></p> <p>This is a great idea. It's clever and I absolutely adore it. I thought for a moment that 4215's return was omitted but I saw it before I posted this critique. That incident log doesn't really mention any attempt to re-contain 4215 however, it just goes eco-terrorist and then retreats when it's finished. I feel like the Foundation would at least send an MTF? Regardless I still really like this SCP.</p> <p><strong>SQUID TANK SQUAD +1</strong></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12270315#post-4422267</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12270315/scp-4215#post-4422267</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 13 Nov 2019 18:11:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Thomas Michael Hood</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1409090</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I’ll admit, the idea of a bunch of cuttlefish operating a discarded heavy-duty battle machine is hilarious. The fact that it’s cuttlefish to begin with (a group of cephalopods rarely represented as characters in fiction outside of freely-published &quot;aquatic funny animal&quot; or &quot;anthromorph&quot; settings) makes it even better. I’m a sucker for &quot;species seldom represented in this context&quot; fiction.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
